In article <Zq-TJRk.eca2828@delphi.com> eca2828@delphi.com writes:
>
>        WinCrypt is a windows utility that encrypts files.  It uses
>a 1 to 128 character password.  It takes this password and converts it
>to a 512 character block which it then exclusive ORs to the file.
>This makes sense to me even with my limited encryption knowledge but
>at the end it says something that puzzles me.

This without looking at it further sounds weak to me, exp on large files.
I would also have to take a look at the password to block conversion
routine and see how robust that is.

The major flaw (at least in your description) is that the key repeats
every 512 chars.

